  "text": "Hicks, Mullen, Yucas, and Zavislak [CITATION_1] were able to prove that for m = t + 1, all sequences eventually reach 1. Therefore the conjecture is true when m = t+1. However, for most choices of m we can easily find nontrivial cycles.",
